obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (43416)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Title and extent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00049_189118_1523337061600&sectionId=43416&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00049_189118_1523337061600
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Bankers Books Evidence Act, 1891.`
  line
  line `(2) It ^1extends to the whole of India ^2[except the State of Jammu and Kashmir]; ^3***`
  line
  line `^4* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The Act has been extended in its application to the whole of the Union territory of Lakshadweep (with effect from 1-10-1967)`
  line `vide Reg. 8 of 1965, s. 3 and the Schedule and to the Union territory of Pondicherry by Act 26 of 1968, s. 3 and the Schedule.`
  line `This Act shall apply in relation to the Development Banks as if that were a bank as defined in section 2 of this Act, vide Act 18`
  line `of 1964, s. 33.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule, for "except Part B State".`
  line
  line `3. The word "and" rep. by Act 10 of 1914, s. 3 and the Second Schedule.`
  line
  line `4. Sub-section (3) rep. by s. 3 and the Second Schedule, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (43417)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00049_189118_1523337061600&sectionId=43417&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00049_189118_1523337061600
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there is something repugnant in the subject or context,--`
  line
  line `^1[(1) company means any company as defined in section 3 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of`
  line `1956), and includes a foreign company within the meaning of section 591 of that Act;`
  line
  line `(1A) corporation means any body corporate established by any law for the time being in force`
  line `in India and includes the Reserve Bank of India, the State Bank of India and any subsidiary bank as`
  line `defined in the State Bank of India (Subsidiary Banks) Act, 1959 (38 of 1959);]`
  line
  line `(2) bank and banker mean--`
  line
  line `^2[(a) any company or corporation carrying on the business of banking;]`
  line
  line `(b) any partnership or individual to whose books the provisions of this Act shall have been`
  line `extended as hereinafter provided;`
  line
  line `^3[(c) any post office savings bank or money order office;`
  line
  line `^4[(3) bankers' books include ledgers, day-books, cash-books, account books and all other records`
  line `used in the ordinary business of the bank, whether these records are kept in written form or stored in a`
  line `micro film, magnetic tape or in any other form of mechanical or electronic data retrieval mechanism,`
  line `either onsite or at any offsite location including a back-up or disaster recovery site of both;]`
  line
  line `^5[(4) legal proceeding means,--`
  line
  line `(i) any proceeding or inquiry in which evidence is or may be given;`
  line
  line `(ii) an arbitration; and`
  line
  line `(iii) any investigation or inquiry under the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), or`
  line `under any other law for the time being in force for the collection of evidence, conducted by a`
  line `police officer or by any other person (not being a magistrate) authorised in this behalf by a`
  line `magistrate or by any law for the time being in force;]`
  line
  line `(5) the Court means the person or persons before whom a legal proceeding is held or taken;`
  line
  line `(6) Judge means a Judge of a High Court Division;`
  line
  line `(7) trial means any hearing before the Court at which evidence is taken; and`
  line
  line `^6[(8) certified copy means when the books of a bank,`
  line
  line `(a) are maintained in written form, a copy of any entry in such books together with a`
  line `certificate written at the foot of such copy that it is a true copy of such entry, that such entry`
  line `is contained in one of the ordinary books of the bank and was made in the usual and ordinary`
  line `course of business and that such books is still in the custody of the bank, and where the copy`
  line `was obtained by mechanical or other process which in itself ensured the accuracy of the copy,`
  line `a further certificate to that effect, but where the book from which such copy was prepared has`
  line `been destroyed in the usual course of the bank's business after the date on which the copy has`
  line `been so prepared, a further certificate to that effect, each such certificate being dated and`
  line `subscribed by the principal accountant or manager of the bank with his name and official`
  line `title; and`
  line
  line `(b) consists of printouts of data stored in a floppy, disc, tape or any other`
  line `electro-magnetic data storage device, a printout of such entry or a copy of such printout`
  line `together with such statements certified in accordance with the provisions of section 2A.`
  line
  line `^7[(c) a printout of any entry in the books of a bank stored in a micro film, magnetic tape`
  line `or in any other form of mechanical or electronic data retrieval mechanism obtained by a`
  line `mechanical or other process which in itself ensures the accuracy of such printout as a copy of`
  line `such entry and such printout contains the certificate in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `section 2A.]`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 56 of 1962, s. 4, for clause (1).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for sub-clause (a)`
  line
  line `3. Added by Act 1 of 1893, s. 2.`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 55 of 2002, s. 11, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 6-2-2003).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 1 of 1984, s. 2, for clause (4) (w.e.f. 15-2-1984).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 21 of 2000, s. 93 and the third Schedule, for sub-section (8) (w.e.f. 17-10-2000).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 55 of 2002, s. 11 (w.e.f. 6-2-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_2_a:
  sectionId (75162)
  sectionNo 2A
  orderNo 3
  title `Conditions in the printout.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 2000, s. 93 and the third Schedule (w.e.f. 17-10-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00049_189118_1523337061600&sectionId=75162&sectionno=2A&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00049_189118_1523337061600
obj_root_law_sections_2_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[2-A. Conditions in the printout.A printout of entry or a copy of printout referred to in`
  line `sub-section (8) of section 2 shall be accompanied by the following, namely:`
  line
  line `(a) a certificate to the effect that it is a printout of such entry or a copy of such printout by the`
  line `principal accountant or branch manager ; and`
  line
  line `(b) a certificate by a person in-charge of computer system containing a brief descriptions of the`
  line `computer system and the particulars of--`
  line
  line `(A) the safeguards adopted by the system to ensure that data is entered or any other operation`
  line `performed only by authorised persons;`
  line
  line `(B) the safeguards adopted to prevent and detect unauthorised change of data;`
  line
  line `(C) the safeguards available to retrieve data that is lost due to systemic failure or any other`
  line reasons;
  line
  line `(D) the manner in which data is transferred from the system to removable media like floppies,`
  line `discs, tapes or other electro-magnetic data storage devices;`
  line
  line `(E) the mode of verification in order to ensure that data has been accurately transferred to`
  line `such removable media;`
  line
  line `(F) the mode of identification of such data storage devices;`
  line
  line `(G) the arrangements for the storage and custody of such storage devices;`
  line
  line `(H) the safeguards to prevent and detect any tampering with the system; and any other factor`
  line `which will vouch for the integrity and accuracy of the system.`
  line
  line `(c) a further certificate from the person in-charge of the computer system to the effect that to the`
  line `best of his knowledge and behalf, such computer system operated properly at the material time, he`
  line `was provided with all the relevant data and the printout in question represents correctly, or is`
  line `appropriately derived from, the relevant data.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (43418)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 4
  title `Power to extend provisions of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00049_189118_1523337061600&sectionId=43418&sectionno=3&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00049_189118_1523337061600
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `The State Government may, from time to time, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, extend the provisions of this Act to the books of any partnership or`
  line `individual carrying on the business of bankers within the territories under its administration, and keeping`
  line `a set of not less than three ordinary account-books, namely, a cashbook, a day-book or journal, and a`
  line `ledger, and may in like manner rescind any such notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (43419)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 5
  title `Mode of proof of entries in bankers’ books.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00049_189118_1523337061600&sectionId=43419&sectionno=4&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00049_189118_1523337061600
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act, a certified`
  line `copy of any entry in a banker's book shall in all legal proceedings be received as prima facie evidence of`
  line `the existence of such entry, and shall be admitted as evidence of the matters, transactions and accounts`
  line `therein recorded in every case where, and to the same extent as, the original entry itself is now by law`
  line `admissible, but not further or otherwise.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (43420)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 6
  title `Case in which officer of bank not compellable to produce books.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00049_189118_1523337061600&sectionId=43420&sectionno=5&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00049_189118_1523337061600
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `No officer of a bank shall in`
  line `any legal proceeding to which the bank is not a party be compellable to produce any bankers book the`
  line `contents of which can be proved under this Act, or to appear as a witness to prove the matters,`
  line `transactions and accounts therein recorded, unless by order of the Court or a Judge made for special`
  line cause.
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (43421)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 7
  title `Inspection of books by order of Court or Judge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00049_189118_1523337061600&sectionId=43421&sectionno=6&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00049_189118_1523337061600
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) On the application of any party to a legal`
  line `proceeding the Court or a Judge may order that such party be at liberty to inspect and take copies of any`
  line `entries in a bankers book for any of the purposes of such proceeding, or may order the bank to prepare`
  line `and produce, within a time to be specified in the order, certified copies of all such entries, accompanied`
  line `by a further certificate that no other entries are to be found in the books of the bank relevant to the matters`
  line `in issue in such proceeding, and such further certificate shall be dated and subscribed in manner`
  line `hereinbefore directed in reference to certified copies.`
  line
  line `(2) An order under this or the preceding section may be made either with or without summoning the`
  line `bank, and shall be served on the bank three clear days (exclusive of bank holidays) before the same is to`
  line `be obeyed, unless the Court or Judge shall otherwise direct.`
  line
  line `(3) The bank may at any time before the time limited for obedience to any such order as aforesaid`
  line `either offer to produce their books at the trial or give notice of their intention to show cause against such`
  line `order, and thereupon the same not be enforced without further order.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (43422)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 8
  title Costs.
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00049_189118_1523337061600&sectionId=43422&sectionno=7&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00049_189118_1523337061600
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The costs of any application to the Court or a Judge under or for the purposes of this`
  line `Act and the costs of anything done or to be done under an order of the Court or a Judge made under or for`
  line `the purposes of this Act shall be in the discretion of the Court or Judge, who may further order such costs`
  line `or any part thereof to be paid to any party by the bank if they have been incurred in consequence of any`
  line `fault or improper delay on the part of the bank.`
  line
  line `(2) Any order made under this section for the payment of costs to or by a bank may be enforced as if`
  line `the bank were a party to the proceeding.`
  line
  line `(3) Any order under this section awarding costs may, on application to any Court of Civil Judicature`
  line `designated in the order, be executed by such Court as if the order were a decree for money passed by`
  line `itself:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall be construed to derogate from any power which the`
  line `Court or Judge making the order may possess for the enforcement of its or his directions with respect to`
  line `the payment of costs.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (43423)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 9
  title `Order of court to be construed to be order made by specified officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 1 of 1984, s. 2 (w.e.f. 15-2-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00049_189118_1523337061600&sectionId=43423&sectionno=8&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00049_189118_1523337061600
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `^1[8. Order of court to be construed to be order made by specified officer.-- In the application of`
  line `sections 5, 6 and 7 to any investigation or inquiry referred to in sub-clause (iii) of clause (4) of section 2,`
  line `the order of al Court or a Judge referred to in the said sections shall be construed as referring to an order`
  line `made by an officer of a rank not lower than the rank of a Superintendent of Police as may be specified in`
  line `this behalf by the appropriate Government.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In the this section, "appropriate Government" means the Government by which the`
  line `police officer or any other person conducting the investigation or inquiry is employed.`
obj_root_law_translations:
  hi obj_root_law_translations_hi
